{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860138094,"sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","part":{"id":"prt_d79833cfb001dlZvTPXzzHZcsL","messageID":"msg_d79832c1d001tIAghBbFJaMiE4","sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c0d4ba27b4cc46ae8509e8ed7df103a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775860138083,"end":1775860138092}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860138105,"sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","part":{"id":"prt_d7983404a001nS0F7iRsrnRqHa","messageID":"msg_d79832c1d001tIAghBbFJaMiE4","sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9cf954f1b87248d78bad4e0e9e6df5ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement Redis and Valkey storage backends for AgentCube session management, providing high-performance, persistent storage with dual-provider support. This implementation provides:\n6: \n7: 1. **Dual Backend Support**: Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`) implementations selectable via `STORE_TYPE`\n8: 2. **Session Metadata Persistence**: Store `SandboxInfo` JSON documents keyed by session ID\n9: 3. **GC Indexes**: Sorted sets for expiry-based and last-activity-based garbage collection queries\n10: 4. **Singleton Pattern**: Thread-safe initialization via `sync.Once` with klog fatal on failure\n11: 5. **Atomic Operations**: Pipeline/multi-command batching for store/delete operations\n12: 6. **Graceful Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with 9 methods: Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n21: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Provider constants (`redis`, `valkey`), `Storage()` singleton accessor, `initStore()` initialization logic |\n22: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | `redisStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `go-redis/v9` |\n23: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | `valkeyStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `valkey-go` |\n24: | `pkg/store/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n25: | `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Unit tests for interface compliance, error handling, edge cases |\n26: \n27: ### Key Components\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/store/\n31: ├── Store interface (store.go)\n32: │   ├── Ping(ctx) error\n33: │   ├── GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n34: │   ├── StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity (pipeline)\n35: │   ├── UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SET XX only\n36: │   ├── DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error — DEL + ZREM (pipeline)\n37: │   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n38: │   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n39: │   ├── UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n40: │   └── Close() error\n41: │\n42: ├── Errors (store.go)\n43: │   └── ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n44: │\n45: ├── Singleton (singleton.go)\n46: │   ├── redisStoreType = \"redis\"\n47: │   ├── valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n48: │   ├── initStoreOnce = sync.Once{}\n49: │   ├── provider Store\n50: │   ├── Storage() Store → initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n51: │   └── initStore() error → reads STORE_TYPE, builds provider\n52: │\n53: ├── Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n54: │   ├── redisStore struct\n55: │   │   ├── cli *redisv9.Client\n56: │   │   ├── sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n57: │   │   ├── expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n58: │   │   └── lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n59: │   ├── Environment: REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\n60: │   └── Commands: PING, GET, SETNX, SET XX, DEL, ZADD, ZREM, ZRANGEBYSCORE\n61: │\n62: ├── Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n63: │   ├── valkeyStore struct\n64: │   │   ├── cli valkey.Client\n65: │   │   ├── Same key constants as Redis\n66: │   ├── Environment: VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated), VALKEY_PASSWORD, VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED, VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE, VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n67: │   └── API: B().Ping(), B().Get(), DoMulti (SETNX/ZADD/ZADD), SET XX, Zrangebyscore, Mget\n68: │\n69: └── Test Coverage (store_test.go)\n70:     ├── Ping connectivity\n71:     ├── CRUD operations\n72:     ├── ZSET index operations\n73:     ├── ErrNotFound scenarios\n74:     ├── Nil/zero validation\n75:     ├── Missing key tolerance in List*\n76:     ├── Singleton initialization\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Out of Scope\n80: \n81: - Redis Cluster deployment (single-node focus; Valkey supports comma-separated addresses)\n82: - Distributed lock implementation\n83: - Cache preheating strategy\n84: - Data migration tools\n85: - Redis Sentinel support\n86: - Session data encryption\n87: - Rate limiting on storage operations\n88: - Watch/subscribe for real-time updates\n89: \n90: ## Impact Analysis\n91: \n92: ### Upstream Dependencies\n93: \n94: | Dependency | Impact |\n95: |------------|--------|\n96: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library — Redis implementation |\n97: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library — Valkey implementation |\n98: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging singleton init failure |\n99: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct definition |\n100: | `context` | Operation timeout/cancellation support |\n101: | `encoding/json` | SandboxInfo serialization |\n102: | `time` | Timestamp handling for expiry/activity |\n103: | `sync` | Singleton initialization guard |\n104: \n105: ### Downstream Consumers\n106: \n107: | Consumer | Usage |\n108: |----------|-------|\n109: | Session Manager (`pkg/router/session_manager.go`) | Query/create/update sessions via `Storage()` |\n110: | Router (`pkg/router/server.go`) | Session lookup for request routing |\n111: | Workload Manager (`pkg/workloadmanager/`) | Create sandbox → `StoreSandbox`; delete → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n112: | Garbage Collector (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup |\n113: \n114: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n115: \n116: - **Store Interface Signature**: Adding/removing methods requires all implementations to update\n117: - **Key Pattern Changes**: Changing `session:` prefix or ZSET keys breaks existing data\n118: - **Environment Variable Names**: Rename requires deployment updates\n119: - **ErrNotFound Message**: Changing `store: not found` message breaks error comparison\n120: - **SandboxInfo Fields**: Missing JSON tags or new fields affect stored documents\n121: - **Singleton Fatal Behavior**: `klog.Fatalf` on init failure crashes process; must handle env validation before production\n122: \n123: ## Alternatives Considered\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 1: Single Redis Backend Only\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Implement only Redis, skip Valkey support.\n128: \n129: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n130: |--------|------------|\n131: | Pros | Simpler codebase; single dependency; fewer tests |\n132: | Cons | Locks into Redis vendor; Valkey is open-source Redis alternative with better licensing; limits deployment flexibility |\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Rejected. Valkey is LF-supported Redis fork; dual support provides vendor flexibility without significant complexity overhead (same data model, similar APIs).\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 2: In-Memory Storage\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Use `sync.Map` or map with mutex for in-memory storage.\n139: \n140: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n141: |--------|------------|\n142: | Pros | No external dependency; simpler deployment; fast local access |\n143: | Cons | No persistence (restart loses data); no distributed access; no GC indexes without custom implementation |\n144: \n145: **Decision**: Rejected. Production requires persistence for session continuity across restarts and distributed access for multi-instance deployment.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 3: Etcd Storage\n148: \n149: **Approach**: Use Etcd as storage backend.\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n152: |--------|------------|\n153: | Pros | Strong consistency; Kubernetes-native; built-in watch/lease |\n154: | Cons | Higher latency than Redis/Valkey; heavier resource footprint; overkill for session metadata |\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Rejected. Session storage prioritizes low-latency reads/writes over strong consistency. Redis/Valkey sorted sets provide efficient expiry/activity queries.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 4: Database Storage (PostgreSQL/MySQL)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Use relational database with session table and indexed columns.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | Strong consistency; familiar SQL queries; existing DB infrastructure |\n165: | Cons | Higher latency; heavier for simple key-value patterns; connection pool complexity |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. Session data is simple key-value with time-based queries. Redis/Valkey sorted sets are optimal for `ZRANGEBYSCORE` expiry/inactivity lookups.\n168: \n169: ### Alternative 5: Pipeline vs. Individual Commands\n170: \n171: **Approach**: Execute `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as separate commands without pipeline.\n172: \n173: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n174: |--------|------------|\n175: | Pros | Simpler code; easier error handling per command |\n176: | Cons | Multiple round trips; partial success leaves inconsistent state (key exists without ZSET entry) |\n177: \n178: **Decision**: Rejected. Pipeline/multi ensures atomic batch: all commands succeed or fail together, maintaining consistency between session key and ZSET indexes.\n179: \n180: ## Risks\n181: \n182: | Risk | Mitigation |\n183: |------|------------|\n184: | Redis/Valkey connection failure | Env validation on init; `Ping` for health check; singleton fatal catches early |\n185: | Missing password with required=true | Explicit check: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable |\n186: | ZSET orphan members (key deleted, ZSET entry remains) | `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` skips missing keys without error |\n187: | Key collision across namespaces | Key pattern `session:{sessionID}` uses globally unique session ID |\n188: | Pipeline partial failure | Redis pipeline returns all errors; Valkey `DoMulti` fails on any error |\n189: | Clock skew for expiry scoring | Unix timestamp scoring is absolute; relies on server clock accuracy |\n190: | Singleton race condition | `sync.Once` guarantees single initialization |\n191: | Valkey MGET slot requirement | Comment notes keys should be in same slot; deployment must ensure consistent hashing |\n192: \n193: ## Implementation Notes\n194: \n195: 1. **Key Pattern**: `session:{sessionID}` for JSON documents\n196: 2. **Expiry ZSET**: `session:expiry` — member = sessionID, score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n197: 3. **Activity ZSET**: `session:last_activity` — member = sessionID, score = `at.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n198: 4. **SETNX for Store**: Prevents duplicate session creation\n199: 5. **SET XX for Update**: Enforces key must exist before update\n200: 6. **ZRANGEBYSCORE**: `-inf` to `{before.Unix()}` for expiry/inactivity queries\n201: 7. **ErrNotFound**: Redis `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`; Valkey `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n202: 8. **STORE_TYPE**: Case-insensitive; defaults to `redis`; only `redis` or `valkey` accepted\n203: 9. **Password Required**: Default true; set `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` or `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable\n204: 10. **Singleton Fatal**: `initStore` error → `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`; process exits\n205: \n206: ## References\n207: \n208: - `session-store/design.md` — Detailed design specification\n209: - `session-store/spec.md` — Requirements and scenarios\n210: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo` struct definition\n211: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client reference\n212: - `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` — Related interface definition (if exists)\n213: - [go-redis v9](https://github.com/redis/go-redis)\n214: - [valkey-go](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go)\n\n(End of file - total 214 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement Redis and Valkey storage backends for AgentCube session management, providing high-performance, persistent storage with dual-provider support. This implementation provides:\n\n1. **Dual Backend Support**: Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`) implementations selectable via `STORE_TYPE`\n2. **Session Metadata Persistence**: Store `SandboxInfo` JSON documents keyed by session ID\n3. **GC Indexes**: Sorted sets for expiry-based and last-activity-based garbage collection queries\n4. **Singleton Pattern**: Thread-safe initialization via `sync.Once` with klog fatal on failure\n5. **Atomic Operations**: Pipeline/multi-command batching for store/delete operations\n6. **Graceful Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with 9 methods: Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775860138086,"end":1775860138103}}}}
