{"type":"text","timestamp":1775860246557,"sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","part":{"id":"prt_d79836ac1001dLMaxgmc4JEKJ3","messageID":"msg_d798340a0001RuGs3mJbBowr6P","sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the comprehensive proposal.md for AR-015.","time":{"start":1775860246552,"end":1775860246552}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860246605,"sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","part":{"id":"prt_d7984e81b0013udNdGuvTmb6bS","messageID":"msg_d798340a0001RuGs3mJbBowr6P","sessionID":"ses_2867db7d1ffexeCjjrX88vSoAA","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a77ca113259b43dc99302be6b33d449f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","content":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement PicoD (Pico Daemon), an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. This enables AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files through a JWT-protected REST API.\n\n**Current State**: PicoD implementation does not exist in the codebase. The `pkg/picod` package is empty/missing, and `cmd/picod` entrypoint is not defined.\n\n**Target State**: Fully functional PicoD daemon with:\n- `POST /api/execute` — Execute shell commands with timeout, working directory, and environment control\n- `POST /api/files` — Upload files (multipart or JSON/Base64)\n- `GET /api/files?path=...` — List directory contents\n- `GET /api/files/*path` — Download files\n- `GET /health` — Unauthenticated health endpoint\n- JWT RS256 authentication via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Workspace jail with path traversal protection\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/config.go` | `Config` struct with Port, Workspace; CLI flag parsing logic |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` | Gin engine setup, route registration, workspace resolution, HTTP server lifecycle |\n| `pkg/picod/auth.go` | `AuthManager` struct, RSA public key loading from PEM, JWT middleware with MaxBytesReader |\n| `pkg/picod/execute.go` | ExecuteRequest/ExecuteResponse structs, command execution handler with context timeout |\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` | FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs; upload, list, download handlers |\n| `pkg/picod/health.go` | Health check handler with uptime tracking |\n| `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` | `sanitizePath` function for workspace jail security (symlink resolution, path traversal check) |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Entrypoint with klog flags, CLI flag parsing (`-port`, `-workspace`), `NewServer`, `Run` |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Unit tests for execute, file operations, authentication, path sanitization |\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n#### Server Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int    `json:\"port\"`\n    Workspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n}\n```\n\n- CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default empty → CWD)\n- Workspace resolution: `os.Getwd()` if empty; `filepath.Abs` for relative paths\n- HTTP server: `ReadHeaderTimeout` = 10 seconds\n\n#### Constants\n\n| Name | Value | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n| `maxFileMode` | `0777` | Maximum file mode; reject > 0777 |\n| Default timeout | `60 * time.Second` | Execute timeout when request field empty |\n| Default file mode | `0644` | File creation mode when mode invalid/empty |\n\n#### Request/Response Structures\n\n**Execute**:\n```go\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Files**:\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n}\n\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Route Registration\n\n```go\nengine := gin.New()\nengine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())\n\napi := engine.Group(\"/api\")\napi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n{\n    api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n    api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n}\nengine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n```\n\n#### JWT Authentication (`AuthManager`)\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\n- Load from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` PEM (PKIX format)\n- Middleware: Require `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n- Parse with `jwt.Parse` + `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, `WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n- Reject non-RSA signing methods (HS256 rejected)\n- On valid token: `http.MaxBytesReader` with `MaxBodySize`\n\n#### Path Security (`sanitizePath`)\n\n1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks via `filepath.EvalSymlinks`)\n2. Clean requested path; strip leading `/` if absolute\n3. Join with workspace root\n4. Verify `filepath.Rel` does not start with `..`\n5. If path exists: re-validate resolved path against workspace\n6. Return sanitized absolute path\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Stdin support for executed commands\n- WebSocket-based streaming stdout/stderr\n- File deletion API\n- Directory creation API\n- File permissions modification API\n- Symlink creation/resolution API\n- Archive (tar/zip) operations\n- Multiple workspace roots\n- JWT refresh/rotation\n- Rate limiting per session\n- Command history/audit logging\n- Process kill/signal API\n- Background/async command execution\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework; route registration, middleware, JSON binding |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing; RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, fatal logging on auth key missing |\n| `os/exec` | Standard | `exec.CommandContext` for command execution |\n| `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n| `base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n| `filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| CodeInterpreter Sandbox Pods | `POST /api/execute` for Python/shell code execution; file APIs for workspace management |\n| Agent Runtime Sandbox Pods | `POST /api/execute` for agent tool execution; file APIs for artifact storage |\n| Router JWT Issuer | Generates RS256 tokens validated by PicoD's public key |\n| Workload Manager | Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` into sandbox pod environment |\n| Python SDK | Calls PicoD APIs for code execution and file operations |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Auth Key Requirement**: Missing/invalid `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` causes fatal startup failure — deployment must provide valid PEM\n- **Timeout Behavior**: Change from 60s default affects existing clients without explicit timeout\n- **Exit Code 124**: Timeout uses specific exit code; clients must handle this\n- **Path Security**: Stricter sanitization may reject previously accepted paths (e.g., symlink escapes)\n- **MaxBodySize**: 32 MiB limit may reject large file uploads\n\n### Compatibility Notes\n\n1. **RSA JWT Only**: PicoD rejects HS256 tokens; Router must issue RS256\n2. **No Stdin**: Commands cannot receive input from client; stdin not connected\n3. **Workspace Jail**: All file paths relative to workspace root; absolute paths stripped of leading `/`\n4. **Gin ReleaseMode**: Default mode; no debug logging in production\n5. **Public Key PEM**: PKIX format (`PUBLIC KEY` block), not PKCS#1 (`RSA PUBLIC KEY`)\n6. **File Mode Octal**: `parseFileMode` uses `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: WebSocket Streaming Commands\n\n**Approach**: Use WebSocket for bidirectional command execution with real-time stdout/stderr streaming.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Real-time output; stdin support; better for long-running commands |\n| Cons | More complex protocol; connection management overhead; Gin WebSocket integration extra dependency |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Initial implementation targets simple request/response pattern. WebSocket can be added later as enhancement without breaking existing clients.\n\n### Alternative 2: SSH-based Execution\n\n**Approach**: Expose SSH server inside sandbox for command execution.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Standard protocol; existing tooling; stdin support |\n| Cons | SSH key management complexity; port conflicts; harder to proxy through Router |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. HTTP API integrates better with Router's reverse proxy architecture. JWT auth matches Router's token issuance pattern.\n\n### Alternative 3: gRPC API\n\n**Approach**: Use gRPC for command execution and file operations.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Strong typing; streaming support; efficient binary protocol |\n| Cons | Requires gRPC client in SDK; Router proxy complexity; heavier for simple file operations |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. HTTP/JSON matches Router's HTTP routing. gRPC could be added as alternate transport without removing HTTP API.\n\n### Alternative 4: Container Runtime API (Docker/Kubernetes exec)\n\n**Approach**: Use `kubectl exec` or Docker API to run commands in containers.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No in-container daemon; uses existing container runtime |\n| Cons | Requires kubelet/Docker API access; not available from inside pod; latency for API calls |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. PicoD runs inside sandbox pod for low-latency local execution. Container runtime API requires external orchestration.\n\n### Alternative 5: Separate File Service\n\n**Approach**: Split file operations into separate daemon from command execution.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Independent scaling; separate auth policies |\n| Cons | More deployment complexity; two services per sandbox; shared workspace coordination |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Single daemon simplifies deployment. Both operations share same workspace jail and auth context.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Missing auth public key at startup | `klog.Fatalf` with clear error message; deployment checklist must include PEM generation |\n| Invalid PEM format | `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` validates PEM decode + PKIX parse; returns error to `NewServer` |\n| Command timeout runaway | `exec.CommandContext` with deadline; process killed when context cancelled |\n| Path traversal via symlink | `sanitizePath` resolves symlinks; re-validates resolved path against workspace |\n| Large file upload DoS | `MaxBodySize` = 32 MiB applied after JWT validation |\n| JWT replay attacks | `WithExpirationRequired` + `WithIssuedAt` enforced; leeway 1 minute |\n| Non-RSA JWT method attack | Middleware type-assert `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`; reject HS256/other |\n| Process fork bomb | Timeout limits duration; no stdin prevents interactive loops |\n| Missing workspace directory | `os.Getwd` failure → fatal; `filepath.Abs` validates configured path |\n| Race on public key reload | `AuthManager` uses `sync.RWMutex` for public key access |\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n1. **Package Structure**\n   - Create `pkg/picod/` directory\n   - Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n   - Create `cmd/picod/main.go` entrypoint\n\n2. **Server Setup**\n   - `NewServer` constructs Gin engine with ReleaseMode\n   - Register global Logger/Recovery middleware\n   - Resolve workspace directory (CWD fallback)\n   - Store `startTime` for health uptime\n\n3. **Authentication**\n   - `AuthManager` struct with RSA public key\n   - `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` — read PEM, decode, parse PKIX\n   - Fatal on missing/invalid key\n   - `AuthMiddleware` — Bearer extraction, JWT parse, RSA method check\n   - Apply `http.MaxBytesReader` on valid token\n\n4. **Execute Handler**\n   - Bind `ExecuteRequest` from JSON\n   - Parse timeout string → `time.Duration`\n   - `exec.CommandContext` with timeout context\n   - Capture stdout/stderr to `bytes.Buffer`\n   - Handle `context.DeadlineExceeded` → exit code 124\n   - Return `ExecuteResponse` with duration, timestamps\n\n5. **File Upload Handler**\n   - Detect multipart vs JSON via Content-Type prefix\n   - Multipart: `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, optional mode\n   - JSON: Base64 decode `UploadFileRequest.Content`\n   - Create parent directories (0755)\n   - Write file with parsed mode (default 0644)\n   - Return `FileInfo` with relative path\n\n6. **File List Handler**\n   - Query parameter `path` required\n   - `os.ReadDir` on sanitized path\n   - Build `FileEntry` array; skip failed `entry.Info()`\n   - Return `ListFilesResponse`\n\n7. **File Download Handler**\n   - Wildcard path parameter `*path`\n   - Strip leading `/` before sanitization\n   - Verify path is file (not directory)\n   - Set download headers: Content-Disposition, Content-Type\n   - Use `c.File` for streaming\n\n8. **Health Handler**\n   - No auth middleware\n   - Return JSON: status \"ok\", service \"PicoD\", version \"0.0.1\", uptime string\n\n9. **Path Sanitization**\n   - `sanitizePath` function\n   - Resolve workspace symlinks\n   - Clean and join path\n   - Check `filepath.Rel` for `..` escape\n   - Re-validate if path exists (follow symlinks)\n\n10. **Tests**\n    - Execute: valid command, timeout, invalid timeout, empty command, working directory, env augmentation\n    - Files: multipart upload, JSON Base64 upload, invalid Base64, list success, list missing path, download success, path escape, not a file\n    - Auth: missing header, invalid format, expired JWT, non-RSA method\n    - Health: unauthenticated access\n\n## References\n\n- `code-execution/spec.md` — PicoD requirements and scenarios\n- `code-execution/design.md` — Implementation details from reference repo\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n- `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n- `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Container build for PicoD\n- [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin)\n- [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go\">\nERROR [18:2] error while importing k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes: missing go.sum entry for module providing package github.com/google/go-cmp/cmp (imported by k8s.io/client-go/util/consistencydetector); to add:\n\tgo get k8s.io/client-go/util/consistencydetector@v0.31.0\nERROR [18:2